<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="G1" checkit-title="Area">
    <statement>
        <p> A circle has had a 90 degree slice removed from the bottom left portion of the circle and a square is attached cleanly to the missing section of the circle. The dimensions of the shape are as follows: The circle has radius 8, where everything is measured in inches.
            <ol>
                <li>Sketch a drawing of this situation to the best of your ability.</li>
                <li>Find the total area of this shape.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The volume is <m>A \approx 214.8</m> <m>in^2</m>. This was computed using the formula <me>A = \frac{3}{4}\pi r^2 + s^2</me>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
